 Equipment Management: Oversee the installation, testing, and commissioning of new electrical equipment, including Variable Frequency Drives (VFDs), MCC panels, and LV distribution systems.
 System Focus: Maintain the electrical systems for core foundry machinery, including induction furnaces, EOT cranes, sand preparation plants, molding machines, and finishing equipment.
 Safety & Compliance: Ensure strict adherence to all electrical safety norms, industry standards (e.g., OSHA), and lockout-tagout procedures.
 Troubleshooting: Diagnose and fix faults related to PLCs, SCADA systems, motor controls, and instrumentation to ensure minimal production disruption.
 Inventory & Documentation: Manage the inventory of critical electrical spare parts and maintain detailed records of maintenance activities, equipment performance, and downtime reports.
 Team Collaboration: Collaborate with production and mechanical maintenance teams to address cross-functional issues and mentor junior technicians on proper maintenance procedures.
